= Introduction

This section is defined in a separate file and included from the main document.

The famous identity $e = lim_(n -> infinity) (1 + 1/n)^n$ is one way to define Euler's number.

More generally, the exponential function satisfies:

$
  e^x = sum_(n=0)^infinity frac(x^n, n!)
$ <eq-exp-series>

This converges for all $x in RR$.
